-- Seoul shares down for 4th day on geopolitical anxiety, won recovers
-- By Choonsik Yoo
-- Fri Aug 08, 2014 02:17AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, Aug 8 (Reuters) - Seoul shares fell for a fourth consecutive session on Friday, slipping over 1 percent on concerns the escalating geopolitical tensions in Ukraine and Iraq may dent global growth.

The benchmark KOSPI <.KS11> fell 1.14 percent to 2,031.10 points. For the week, the market lost 2.03 percent, snapping a three-week gaining streak.